From cd691efcc74f4cc096fa5b0171a1ff2117976404 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: eoinmcdonnell-glitch <eoin.mcdonnell@instrument.com>
Date: Tue, 21 Jul 2026 00:11:37 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] Add congregation email-invite flow for voting access

- New invitations/invite_tokens tables: admin bulk-invites emails,
  each recipient confirms their own email via a single-use 30-day
  link, then supplies their name and becomes an active member
  (logged in immediately).
- New /api/admin/invitations (POST bulk-send, GET list) and public
  /api/invitations/confirm endpoints.
- Admin page: paste emails, send invitations, view status.
- New /invite/confirm frontend page for the confirmation step.

Also fixes two pre-existing issues found along the way:
- lib/sessions.js was missing entirely; server.js imports
  pruneExpiredSessions from it, so the backend could not start.
- .env.example was missing ADMIN_STUB_KEY, which admin-auth.js
  requires to run.
